This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the development of algorithms for automatic detection of buried threats using ground penetrating radar (GPR) measurements. It also involves the evaluation of these algorithms on a large experimental data set. 

The paper may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category as the algorithms developed may involve the use of neural networks for classification and discrimination tasks. 

The machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category is also likely as the paper deals with the development and evaluation of state-of-the-art algorithms for a specific task. 

The artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also possible as the paper deals with the development of intelligent algorithms for a specific task. 

Finally, the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category is also possible as the paper deals with the development of algorithms for a real-world GPR BTD system, which may involve the use of robotics for data collection and processing.
